article.headline: American 83, Radford 69
article.story: RADFORD, Va. (AP) -- Jason Thomas scored 23 points and American shot 72 percent in the first half Tuesday night in an 83-69 victory against Radford. The Eagles (1-3) were 18-for-25 from the field, including 9-of-13 from beyond the arc, to lead 51-27 at the break. Thomas was 6-for-7 and had 15 points at the half. Whit Holcomb-Faye led Radford (3-2) with 27 points, including a 3-pointer that got the Highlanders within 11 with 2:55 remaining in the game, but they got no closer. Jernavis Draughn and Andre Ingram each added 16 points for the Eagles, who scored the first nine points of the game and closed the first half on an 11-0 run, holding Radford scoreless for the final 5:08 of the half. Andres Rodriguez added eight points, 11 assists and four steals for American.
